ributes like `org_mortbay_jetty.jetty.XmlConfigurationTest$ConfigurableBean`, which might violate NMTOKEN rules. I wonder if I can bypass the DTD. I really should inspect the XmlParser to understand its validation better.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c3a5c965fd6145c0169ff0c5c40dc81968840fbc4e1664132\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_wxrhwzEh14yeUWs5mPtJH-xkJxT5JCWvcjx_olfgVFe0KOesD_i12faiBy4750Asf8YR9KHa5bwLY9ChFO_rmo9vCTI5xVS6ihYBoygmE-31bA_CeXo9U8-EP6UCYB2WgR5KFhizCZtYx8woCrImqrGy4_tZjSvRtade9MLOP6af9PFHjzp_ikwOLxwvLgN1OxXhi1dVHFhiJ1ZhMsNUqsd6pxRlghQMVQByOKBajXq5ZqL9iU8QkeoirHKIzZVL9J7N6iR6nH4Opdoo5C90xxYq8U-di1WR392hVRsO0oNvY5p8WQQEY1Lm5DaCnsnLlfwG1CFO0kHCqn5g7pLpn_bndNI7VWrAYEwxhFaKTaQC-W3DtYquCY5ZLZef-Bh3bO_Gvg-A1QIHDecFNfKMPqfUpJMubtETmSsY7U2T1ZlXPigQNZHLXYOFYPJfpJkFplypjRagWMqm0HsynTbIeG-DxxQLCEn-l-qqXf4S4xglQtfjcnIiyFgD5E7F1iLHIdWT8uFtdx2OvNZP2QqhGOhRxwBX5PY6CFx1wNLDgBeE9gnVhxcYCzIptypRNsFEsBJAIBqFrSv9Gmr9u4BuZyTyWnDrtdE74SZ9OhET56IQEAOOsbGtkG1YJ0mgZCIcEBU1qTF3aYnC2TIZXooY-SOaZZNfeeeLF5NlpPfetpPmOOA1l5D0taRPQsZrMBHiWybXSRAGyMOyrBhDUvyNpOr3qbfWhSKFrOGBfE8CiscWnCbsm9cK3Ayo8iSrv6Bp1104_0OgsVJx33-1kcVVYu-B5W9WJhO_r7kRxmkytTFpt9ljp68oDef7Fa5TWYufddJObnIcHAaZcDuckKdhLVkiuj3FI77CLQ0X8MdUwzPjbgRic78aMyei3XElLONXxoVdquGPxE55X5aijI6IpeHONfjGNVhfeLrgcro76AZuefiCkEFboU7RV5bBpFCMI-ZnbuC5HPwjNVpZm-Lvx0uMkj5keuHJ3B2355z5zJwmD_61JyrQASRc-qYYAIW47ex5SrTp5RWPOIgAmDTzBOxOhNVu3kndFGcwLYFlKPQTm9fp4LRjUyt6FOjANOJlHrfoVIpxeoIo9ByYv9vJAIlrsgJN-0ROZt8xg1uXQRg5BAq7p05oczRrxpAMlQsI6fVsIeBEjLx5PBuTFC8Nn_xo2VGAZmrFpFnU2siTnQMFpd23H8IyDAkZDxFpsU4WnrGWrMPvsQthuvB4w4OJFL_KJyP12aMyKleFizB5JaYyXqRuNxSXwkN8sybj3EE2Z59l1ynE2KRF88_KLjaYiyX8R4ttzugrITUPBP7X9bBZw21O4R9Gf7gxu8KHO4q1HfXZGG9Vr5lr_RZPINT88NzdKLNbKzyQ8NBR7MrbsVQga_Ope4e8Sjzhkvn2_FJMDW26TnlVox9DBHInCn_6albrnK0LMMWrPVfDW_r0bXeARUDRkLh9lf70cN6PAVZQ29oFPa04oTdEWUWbguuL-nie_tTKg-RVitQZSDCpvu712erIQ2xE6N3qkKrj91YXqQPgzn8lbZCsKaY1fQobJuGs3VH2CncRBz8k-BGdGaGNPhcrEibkFeT2JoMSwTZDU4magAHLW-umcd5kXX5UaTHKscKYnPCr